  <p>You’re a natural revolutionary just by being female and living in this world. Why? Because guess who made up the rules. Yeah, that’s right. That’s Hilken Mancini, the co-founder and program director, speaking at the morning assembly (or whatever). We wake up every day, we go to our jobs, feed our kids, walk our dogs, and we don’t really think about it all the time, but we’re punk rock just by being alive. None of this would work without her. She paces the Rock Room, clipboard in hand, words tumbling out by the fistful. Punk isn’t a purple mohawk and ripped fishnets, punk is thinking for yourself. It’s looking at the status quo and going no thanks, I don’t want that, I’m going to do it this way. That’s a really hard thing to do. Picture the silliest combination of clothes you can imagine. Pink tights and gym shorts. A few shirts. Unmatched knee socks and a bedazzled fanny pack. That’s what she’s wearing. It’s hard because we have been living it for a very long time, and it’s hard to see in your everyday life that you’re not supposed to look like anything, you’re not supposed to do anything, you’re not supposed to be this thing that they put on you every day.</p>

